import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce')
    data['month'] = data['date'].dt.month
    avg_temp = data.groupby('month')['temperature'].mean().reset_index()
    chart = sns.lineplot(x='month', y='temperature', data=avg_temp)
    chart.set(xlabel='Month', ylabel='Average Temperature (Fahrenheit)')
    plt.title('What is the average temperature distribution in Seattle throughout the year?', wrap=True)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)

import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['month'] = pd.DatetimeIndex(data['date']).month
    monthly_precipitation = data.groupby('month')['precipitation'].sum().reset_index()
    chart = sns.barplot(x='month', y='precipitation', data=monthly_precipitation)
    chart.set(xlabel='Month', ylabel='Total Precipitation')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of precipitation in Seattle throughout the year?', wrap=True)
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)

import seaborn as sns
import pandas as pd
import matplotlib.pyplot as plt

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['month'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%m/%d/%Y', errors='coerce').dt.month_name()
    data = data.groupby('month')['cloud_cover'].mean().reset_index()
    sns.barplot(x='month', y='cloud_cover', data=data, color='blue')
    plt.title('What is the distribution of cloud cover in Seattle throughout the year?', wrap=True)
    plt.ylim(0, 100)
    plt.ylabel('Average Cloud Cover')
    plt.xlabel('Month')
    return plt;

chart = plot(data)
